<br>
I do like the idea of it being a buff (ultravision, save vs. element, health buff, ac buff, harm shield, etc), and you get penalized for its death.  That is even.  Make the penalty to where some wizzies consider if they want to get one at all (i.e. exp loss back to the point of summoning, exp loss of 1 player death, you dying yourself, debuffed with something like rez effects for a long duration, etc.)  Is the risk worth the reward?<br>
<br>
I do like the idea of it being a random creature (like in D&amp;D), or possibly fail at conjuring one.  We should not be able to pick which one we want imo, this would be too unbalancing.<br>
<br>
I also like the idea of it being persistant.  It should last for a long period of time (forever until it dies).  On the other hand, you should only be able to &quot;find familiar&quot; perhaps 1 per life, or 1 per level, or even several levels.<br>
<br>
We would have to think of some way to keep people from exploiting the system (duel deaths to resummon, dying repeatedly and getting rezzed by cleric uber weapon to get the familiar you want, etc).<br>
<br>
Then there is the question of mobility.  Does it sit on our shoulder?  Does it follow us around?  If it follows us around, it would be subject to bad pathing, accidental agro's, etc.<br>
<br>
It should be a skill that increases with level.  Lower levels should only have a very small chance of finding a good one (they should get a frog, or small bird) normally).  Higher levels should have a good chance of finding a good one (drake, imp, etc).<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts, gotta run.<br>
<br>
